chapter.article:
AGREEMENT 
between the Government of Iceland, of the 
one part, and the Government of Denmark 
and the Home Government of the Faroe 
Islands, of the other part 


The Government of Iceland, of the one part, and the Government of Denmark and the Home Government of the Faroe Islands, of the other part; 

Hereinafter referred to as the CONTRACTING PARTIES; 

WISHING to enhance the economic relations between Iceland and the Faroe Islands and to harmonize their economic development; 

EMPHASIZING fair conditions for competition in a unified market without a customs union; 

DETERMINED to extend their economic relations to generally all sectors of economic activity; 

DETERMINED to develop and enhance their cooperation in other fields; 

HAVE DECIDED to abolish all obstacles to economic relations between Iceland and the Faroe Islands within the substantive scope of this Agreement.
